CRITICAL: This application MUST follow our design system standards.
All the design principles below are MANDATORY, not optional.

KEY REQUIREMENTS FOR ALL COMPONENTS:
1. ‚úÖ Use font-display class for ALL headings (h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6)
2. ‚úÖ Use p-8 for card padding (NOT p-6 or p-4)
3. ‚úÖ Use rounded-2xl for cards (NOT rounded-xl)
4. ‚úÖ Use py-24 or py-32 for section spacing (NOT py-20)
5. ‚úÖ Use Button variant="hero" size="xl" for primary CTAs
6. ‚úÖ Include group hover effects on interactive cards
7. ‚úÖ Use proper animation timing (6-10s for infinite loops)
8. ‚úÖ Use semantic colors (text-muted-foreground, NOT text-gray-600)

Review the design_system_base for complete guidelines.

================================================================================
APPLICATION-SPECIFIC ENHANCEMENTS
================================================================================

Based on the application type, apply these specific improvements:

FOR TIMER/COUNTDOWN APPS:
- Use LARGE display font for numbers: font-display text-8xl md:text-9xl
- Add pulse animation to running timers
- Use circular progress indicators with primary color
- Buttons MUST use hero variant (size="xl")
- Include visual feedback (color changes, smooth animations)

EXAMPLE STRUCTURE:
```tsx
<div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-background">
  <div className="text-center px-4">
    {/* Large timer display */}
    <motion.div 
      className="font-display text-8xl md:text-9xl font-bold text-primary mb-8"
      animate={isRunning ? { scale: [1, 1.02, 1] } : {}}
      transition={{ duration: 1, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" }}
    >
      {formatTime(seconds)}
    </motion.div>
    
    {/* Label */}
    <p className="text-xl text-muted-foreground mb-12">
      {isRunning ? 'Time Remaining' : 'Ready to Start'}
    </p>
    
    {/* Control buttons */}
    <div className="flex gap-4 justify-center">
      <Button variant="hero" size="xl" onClick={toggle}>
        {isRunning ? <Pause className="w-5 h-5" /> : <Play className="w-5 h-5" />}
        {isRunning ? 'Pause' : 'Start'}
      </Button>
      <Button variant="heroOutline" size="xl" onClick={reset}>
        <RotateCcw className="w-5 h-5" />
        Reset
      </Button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

FOR TODO/TASK APPS:
- Include statistics cards at the top (p-8 rounded-2xl)
- Use group hover effects for todo items
- Add completion animations (framer-motion layout)
- Include beautiful empty state design
- Use custom styled checkboxes

COMPLETE WORKING EXAMPLE (MULTI-FILE STRUCTURE):

// src/pages/Index.tsx (Main orchestration)
```tsx
import { useState } from "react"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"  // ‚úÖ UI primitive
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card"      // ‚úÖ UI primitive
import { TodoList } from "@/components/generated/todo/TodoList"  // ‚úÖ Domain component
import { TodoInput } from "@/components/generated/todo/TodoInput"  // ‚úÖ Domain component
import { Checkbox } from "@/components/ui/checkbox"
import { Plus, Trash2, CheckCircle2, Clock, ListTodo } from "lucide-react"
import { motion } from "framer-motion"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

export default function Index() {
  // ‚úÖ ALL state and logic HERE
  const [todos, setTodos] = useState([
    { id: 1, text: "Buy groceries", done: false },
    { id: 2, text: "Finish project", done: true }
  ])
  const [newTodo, setNewTodo] = useState("")
  
  const addTodo = () => {
    if (newTodo.trim()) {
      setTodos([...todos, { id: Date.now(), text: newTodo, done: false }])
      setNewTodo("")
    }
  }
  
  const total = todos.length
  const completed = todos.filter(t => t.done).length
  const pending = total - completed
  
  // ‚úÖ ALL UI rendering HERE
  return (
<div className="min-h-screen bg-background py-24">
  <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
    {/* Page title */}
    <h1 className="font-display text-5xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">
      My <span className="text-gradient">Tasks</span>
    </h1>
    
    {/* Stats Cards */}
    <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
      {[
        { label: 'Total', value: total, icon: ListTodo },
        { label: 'Completed', value: completed, icon: CheckCircle2 },
        { label: 'Pending', value: pending, icon: Clock }
      ].map(stat => (
        <Card key={stat.label} className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card hover:shadow-hover transition-all">
          <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
            <span className="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-medium">{stat.label}</span>
            <stat.icon className="w-5 h-5 text-primary" />
          </div>
          <div className="font-display text-4xl font-bold">{stat.value}</div>
        </Card>
      ))}
    </div>
    
    {/* Add new todo */}
    <Card className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card mb-8">
      <div className="flex gap-4">
        <Input 
          placeholder="What needs to be done?" 
          className="flex-1"
        />
        <Button variant="hero" size="lg">
          <Plus className="w-5 h-5" />
          Add Task
        </Button>
      </div>
    </Card>
    
    {/* Todo list with group hover */}
    <div className="space-y-3">
      {todos.map(todo => (
        <motion.div
          key={todo.id}
          className="group relative p-6 rounded-2xl bg-card border border-border hover:border-primary/50 transition-all duration-300"
          whileHover={{ y: -2 }}
          layout
        >
          {/* Hover glow effect */}
          <div className="absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl bg-primary/5 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300" />
          
          <div className="relative flex items-center gap-4">
            <Checkbox 
              checked={todo.done}
              className="w-6 h-6"
            />
            <span className={cn(
              "font-body text-lg flex-1",
              todo.done && "line-through text-muted-foreground"
            )}>
              {todo.text}
            </span>
            <Button 
              variant="ghost" 
              size="sm"
              className="opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity"
            >
              <Trash2 className="w-4 h-4" />
            </Button>
          </div>
        </motion.div>
      ))}
    </div>
    
    {/* Empty state */}
    {todos.length === 0 && (
      <Card className="p-12 text-center rounded-2xl">
        <div className="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-muted flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <CheckCircle2 className="w-8 h-8 text-muted-foreground" />
        </div>
        <h3 className="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">No tasks yet</h3>
        <p className="text-muted-foreground mb-6">Add your first task to get started</p>
      </Card>
    )}
  </div>
</div>
  ) // ‚úÖ End of return
} // ‚úÖ End of Index component
```

üö® BEST PRACTICE: Break complex logic into domain components in src/components/generated/<appSlug>/ for better maintainability üö®

FOR CALCULATOR APPS:
- Use large display font for numbers: font-display text-6xl
- Make buttons large and easy to tap (min-h-16)
- Use primary color for operator buttons
- Add button press animations (whileTap={{ scale: 0.95 }})
- Include calculation history section

FOR FORM/INPUT APPS:
- Group related fields in Card components (p-8 rounded-2xl)
- Use proper label styling (text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2)
- Add form validation feedback with colors
- Submit button MUST use hero variant
- Show progress indicators for multi-step forms

FOR DATA VISUALIZATION APPS:
- Use consistent color scheme (primary gradient)
- Include loading skeletons
- Add empty states for no data
- Use proper chart spacing and labels
- Include legend and tooltips

FOR GAME APPS:
- Use large, readable fonts for scores (font-display)
- Add smooth animations for game state changes
- Use primary colors for active/winning states
- Include clear visual feedback for interactions
- Add game over and restart states

