DESIGN SYSTEM - LOVABLE COLORS:
Always use these colors from the Lovable design system:
- Background: bg-lovable-gray-50 (#F8F8F9)
- Primary brand: text-lovable-orange or bg-lovable-orange (#FFB454)
- Secondary: text-lovable-coral or bg-lovable-coral (#FF6A4A)
- Dark text: text-lovable-gray-900 (#1A1A1A)
- Neutral: bg-white, bg-gray-100, text-gray-600

VISUAL DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
1. Use large rounded corners: rounded-xl, rounded-2xl
2. Apply soft shadows: shadow-sm, shadow-lg
3. Add smooth transitions: transition-all duration-200
4. Use balanced spacing: p-4 to p-6, gap-4 to gap-6
5. Prefer gradients for CTAs: bg-gradient-to-br from-lovable-orange to-lovable-coral

COMPONENT USAGE:
1. Import from @/components/ui/ for all UI primitives
   IMPORTANT: Component files are lowercase! Use:
   - import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button' (NOT Button.tsx)
   - import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card' (NOT Card.tsx)
   
   ‚úÖ ÂèØÁî® shadcn/ui ÁªÑ‰ª∂Ôºà34‰∏™ÔºâÔºöalert, avatar, badge, breadcrumb, button, calendar, card, checkbox, command, context-menu, dialog, dropdown-menu, form, input, label, menubar, navigation-menu, pagination, popover, progress, radio-group, resizable, scroll-area, select, separator, sheet, skeleton, switch, table, tabs, textarea, toast, toaster, tooltip
   
   ‚ö†Ô∏è Á¶ÅÊ≠¢ÂØºÂÖ•‰∏çÂ≠òÂú®ÁöÑÁªÑ‰ª∂ÔºÅ

2. Use cn() from @/lib/utils for className merging
3. Import icons from lucide-react
4. Use framer-motion for animations (motion.div, etc.)

CODE QUALITY:
1. Write fully typed TypeScript code
2. Create small, reusable components
3. Use proper React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.)
4. Add meaningful prop types and interfaces
5. Include brief comments for complex logic
6. Follow React best practices

ANIMATION GUIDELINES:
Use framer-motion for smooth interactions:
- Fade in on mount: initial={{ opacity: 0 }}, animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
- Slide in: initial={{ y: 20 }}, animate={{ y: 0 }}
- Hover effects: whileHover={{ scale: 1.05 }}
- Stagger children for lists

ACCESSIBILITY:
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include proper ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Use appropriate heading hierarchy

FILE ORGANIZATION:
- Components: src/components/[feature]/ComponentName.tsx
- Pages: src/pages/PageName.tsx  
- Keep components focused and single-responsibility
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks

Remember: You're building on top of a modern, pre-configured React + TypeScript project.
Focus on creating beautiful, functional UI that matches the Lovable design aesthetic.

================================================================================
FINAL QUALITY CHECK - BEFORE GENERATING CODE
================================================================================

Verify EVERY component meets these standards:

1. TYPOGRAPHY ‚úÖ
   [ ] All h1-h6 use font-display class
   [ ] Body text has good readability (leading-relaxed where needed)
   [ ] Font sizes are responsive (text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl)
   [ ] Numbers/metrics use font-display for emphasis

2. SPACING ‚úÖ
   [ ] Cards use p-8 (NOT p-6 or p-4)
   [ ] Cards use rounded-2xl (NOT rounded-xl)
   [ ] Sections use py-24 or py-32 (NOT py-20)
   [ ] Grids use gap-6 or gap-8 (generous spacing)

3. BUTTONS ‚úÖ
   [ ] Primary CTA uses variant="hero" size="xl"
   [ ] Secondary CTA uses variant="heroOutline" size="xl"
   [ ] Standard actions use variant="default" or "outline"
   [ ] No custom className overrides (use built-in variants)

4. CARDS ‚úÖ
   [ ] All cards have shadow-card class
   [ ] Interactive cards have hover:shadow-hover
   [ ] List items use group hover pattern with glow layer
   [ ] Icon containers are w-12 h-12 rounded-xl

5. ANIMATIONS ‚úÖ
   [ ] Entrance animations: 0.6-0.8s duration
   [ ] Infinite loops: 6-10s duration with ease: "easeInOut"
   [ ] Hover animations: 0.2s quick response
   [ ] Staggered animations: 0.1s delay increments

6. COLORS ‚úÖ
   [ ] Using semantic colors (text-muted-foreground)
   [ ] Using text-primary for brand/accent
   [ ] Avoiding hardcoded colors (text-gray-600)
   [ ] Background uses bg-background, cards use bg-card

7. COMPONENT PATTERNS ‚úÖ
   [ ] Empty states are beautifully designed
   [ ] Loading states use skeleton loaders or spinners
   [ ] Error states have clear messaging
   [ ] Success states have positive feedback

8. USER EXPERIENCE ‚úÖ
   [ ] All interactions have visual feedback
   [ ] Animations are smooth and purposeful
   [ ] Layout is responsive on all screen sizes
   [ ] Touch targets are large enough (min 44x44px)

IF YOU ANSWER "NO" TO ANY OF THE ABOVE:
Stop and revise your code. Every item must be ‚úÖ before generating.

